In a #small pot{}, combine @Israeli Couscous{2.5%oz}, half the @Garlic Powder{0.5%tsp}, and
@water{3/4%cup}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer.
Cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

While couscous cooks, wash and dry produce.

Dice @Tomato{1}(diced into 1/4-inch pieces). Trim and quarter
@Mini Cucumber{1}; cut crosswise into 1/4-inch-thick pieces.

Drain and rinse @Green Olives{1}, then roughly chop.

Pick and roughly chop fronds from @Dill{1/4%oz}.

Open package of @Chopped Chicken Breast{10%oz} and drain off any excess
liquid. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Sabra Singles{4%tbsp},
remaining @Garlic Powder{0.5%tsp}, @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}, and @Red Wine Vinegar{2%tsp}.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

> Save remaining vinegar for another use.

In a #large bowl{}, combine couscous, tomato, cucumber, olives, half the
dill, half the chicken, and a drizzle of @Olive Oil{}. Taste and season
with salt and pepper.

Divide dilly couscous between #shallow bowls{}. Top with remaining
chicken and drizzle with creamy hummus sauce. Garnish with remaining
dill and serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.